<!-- This page was broken off from Standing Rules so it may be transcluded there and in other locations such as on [[Security Cameras]] -->
<!-- It remains a part of the Standing Rules. -->
#The Security Camera Policy is the business of the General Membership and as such will be made and amended by a majority vote of the General Membership.
#The Technical Point of Contact for the security camera system will be the Zone Coordinator of the Infrastructure Zone or his designee, who will handle
#* requests to view real-time camera streaming
#* complaints/suggestions about the security camera system at i3 Detroit
#* requests to reposition cameras
#* other issues of technical implementation
#Storage of Footage
#* The past 60 days of footage shall be stored
#* Specific footage may be saved for an indefinite period of time as needed for investigation purposes
#Camera Location and Positioning
#* The current approved list of camera locations is available on the wiki.
#* A camera location can be added or removed from teh current list by a majority vote of the General Membership.
#* Zone Coordinators can position the viewing angle of cameras in their zone.
#Real-Time Camera Access
#* Any member may view real-time security camera footage when at i3 Detroit.
#Request to View Historical Footage
#* A member or members may request to view historical video by contacting the Board of Directors.
#* Footage may be viewed when approved by and accompanied by one member of the Board of Directors and a(nother) member of one of the following groups: the Board of Directors, the Officers, the Zone Coordinators.
#* Information about an approved request will be posted to the mailing list by the Board of Directors, said information to include the requesting member(s) and the specifics of which footage was requested.
#* Non-video/image information from the viewing will be distributed to appropriate members as deemed necessary by the requesting member(s) only.
#Using Recordings
#* If a member or members want to make a copy of historical footage to be copied to any location external to the camera system for whatever (non-commercial?) purpose, every person shown in the footage must be completely removed or blurred out or their consent to be retained on the footage must be secured.
#There are no special physical security measures of the security camera system required by this policy.
#No physically unattended camera may be operated at i3 without being part of and covered by the rules of this Security Camera Policy.
